Final point - thereâ€™s plenty of evidence to show imposter syndrome can be harmful. It means you may work twice as hard to prove your competence and credibility to yourself and others. This can lead to burnout and poor mental health.

PS. I agree imposter syndrome is not always bad - it can encourage humility. BUT, important to recognise whoâ€™s more affected (women, minoritised groups) & how it holds people back. It can lead to the silencing of minoritised voices from public discourse, which is bad for everyone
